# ⚠️  PLACEHOLDER - REPLACE WITH REAL CLOUDFLARE ORIGIN PULL CA CERTIFICATE
# =============================================================================
# NIST SC-8 / SC-13 - TLS Origin Pull Client Authentication
# =============================================================================
# This file must contain the Cloudflare Origin Pull CA certificate used to
# verify that incoming TLS connections originate from Cloudflare's edge.
#
# HOW TO OBTAIN THE REAL CERTIFICATE:
#   1. Cloudflare Dashboard → SSL/TLS → Origin Server
#   2. Download "Cloudflare Origin CA Root Certificate" (ECC or RSA)
#   3. Or fetch directly from Cloudflare's public endpoint:
#      ECC:  https://developers.cloudflare.com/ssl/static/origin_ca_ecc_root.pem
#      RSA:  https://developers.cloudflare.com/ssl/static/origin_ca_rsa_root.pem
#   4. Replace this placeholder with the actual PEM content
#   5. Verify with: openssl x509 -in cloudflare-origin-pull-ca.pem -text -noout
#
# SECURITY NOTE:
#   This file is a PUBLIC CA certificate (not a private key). It is safe to
#   store in git. It enables Caddy's `client_auth` directive to verify that
#   requests come through Cloudflare's proxy, preventing direct-to-origin
#   attacks that bypass Cloudflare's WAF/DDoS protection.
#
# DEPLOYMENT:
#   This file is deployed by roles/stack_ingress/tasks/main.yml only to nodes
#   whose ingress_services entries have `tls_client_auth: cloudflare`.
#
# WARNING:
#   Deploying without replacing this placeholder will cause Caddy to fail
#   TLS handshakes for services with `tls_client_auth: cloudflare`.
#   The preflight assertion in tasks/main.yml will catch this before deploy.
# =============================================================================

-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
REPLACE_ME_WITH_REAL_CLOUDFLARE_ORIGIN_PULL_CA_PEM
-----END CERTIFICATE-----
